value.literal: Type string number directly followed by fret number, followed by a space (e.g.: 10 21 33 11)
Type space as many times as desired to add spacing between notes.
For chords type all 6 string number/fret sets together (e.g.: G major = 635240302313)
For chords with unused strings use xx for string/fret (e.g.: D major = xxxx40322312)
OR... You can just enter a chords name: G for G major; a for a minor.
Type 99 for a single barline, 88 for a double barline.
type <STRING> 51 for a slur mark; 52 for / 53 for \. E.g. if you want a forward slide on string 3, type: 352
